\section{Information criteria}{

AIC and BIC are computed from the \strong{marginal} log-likelihood (i.e. after
integrating out random effects), using the number of \strong{fixed-effect}
parameters as \eqn{k}:
\deqn{AIC = 2k - 2 \ell_m}
\deqn{BIC = k \log(n) - 2 \ell_m}
where \eqn{\ell_m} is the marginal log-likelihood and \eqn{n} is the total
number of data observations.  These values will be \code{NA} when
\code{optimize = FALSE} was passed to \code{\link[=fit_fims]{fit_fims()}}.
